If r is a product of two primes, say r = p*q, then 2r^2 = 2 p^2 q^2, so τ(2r^2) = (1 + 1)(2 + 1)(2 + 1) = 2*3*3 = 18. Then τ(2r^2)/2 = 9. Still too small. If r is a cube of a prime, r = p^3, then 2r^2 = 2 p^6, τ(2p^6) = (1 + 1)(6 + 1) = 2*7 = 14. Then τ(2r^2)/2 = 7. Still less than 14.
